01:01.400 --> 01:02.481
Is this thing real?

01:02.560 --> 01:03.607
Don't play with it.

01:18.960 --> 01:20.325
Have I lost weight?

01:20.400 --> 01:22.243
Was gonna say you look different.

01:22.320 --> 01:24.641
I've lost weight. I mean, I feel good.

01:30.920 --> 01:32.490
It's 50 short.

01:36.400 --> 01:37.401
Get her out of here.

01:39.520 --> 01:41.363
What about my money?

01:41.440 --> 01:43.283
Get your hands off me.

01:43.480 --> 01:45.130
Don't touch me!

01:45.200 --> 01:46.690
You're still fat, Harry.

01:46.760 --> 01:48.171
- Get off!
- Bitch.

02:09.240 --> 02:10.651
Yeah.

02:25.160 --> 02:26.446
OK. Now.

02:36.240 --> 02:37.685
Follow them.

02:53.160 --> 02:56.403
Take a left here,
head to the centre of town.

03:12.240 --> 03:13.571
I'm going in.

03:13.800 --> 03:15.131
There's too many people.

03:15.200 --> 03:17.885
They're gonna go upstairs, find there's
no one there and that'll be it.

03:18.680 --> 03:19.727
No.

03:20.160 --> 03:21.400
Give me your fucking gun.

03:27.120 --> 03:28.201
Wait here.

04:18.600 --> 04:19.761
Excuse me, sir.

04:34.400 --> 04:35.731
Move!

05:06.800 --> 05:09.280
Ah!

07:27.120 --> 07:29.487
He never stated his destination?

07:30.840 --> 07:33.571
He gave his driver instructions
as we went along.

07:35.040 --> 07:36.883
He never suspected
who you worked for?

07:39.280 --> 07:40.281
No.

07:40.360 --> 07:41.600
The Semtex?

07:41.680 --> 07:42.681
It was taken.

07:43.920 --> 07:46.571
I placed a tracer in one of the blocks
the night before.

07:46.920 --> 07:49.082
The tracer went offline
when the attack took place.

07:49.160 --> 07:51.481
We're trying to kick-start it
remotely now.

07:54.000 --> 07:57.482
The perpetrators knew
we were gonna be there at that time.

07:57.920 --> 07:59.081
They knew where we were going.

07:59.160 --> 08:00.525
And you didn't stop them?

08:01.160 --> 08:03.481
Perhaps you don't
belong here any more.

08:04.560 --> 08:07.803
So we've no idea to whom
the Semtex was to be delivered?

08:07.960 --> 08:08.961
No.

08:09.280 --> 08:11.806
You and I, Charlotte, in five.

08:17.040 --> 08:20.089
Difficult times.
He's getting pressures from on high.

08:20.680 --> 08:22.330
You did what you could, Ewan.

08:24.240 --> 08:25.651
Charlotte?

08:29.800 --> 08:31.245
Present from my ex-husband.

08:32.480 --> 08:34.687
Get that seen to and get some rest.

09:19.720 --> 09:21.927
On my break.
I've got two minutes left.

09:22.080 --> 09:24.082
No, I'm not smoking.

09:24.520 --> 09:26.443
I'm not inhaling, I'm walking.

09:26.560 --> 09:28.642
I'm out of breath
cos I had to rush back from lunch.

09:29.840 --> 09:33.481
Tuna sandwich.
Tuna sandwich and some crisps,

09:33.560 --> 09:35.722
and a chocolate biscuit
and a coffee, no sugar.

09:35.800 --> 09:38.929
Hey, we gonna go for drinks? Make it...

09:39.000 --> 09:41.162
about quarter past, yeah?

09:42.360 --> 09:45.011
How's Dad? And the fence?

09:46.520 --> 09:47.885
The garden fence.

09:48.080 --> 09:50.321
Just tell him to wait
and I'll help him the next time I'm up

09:50.400 --> 09:54.200
because his back won't hold up.
I'll get time off. It's not a problem.

09:54.720 --> 09:57.200
I don't know when.
I'll let you know when I know.

09:57.280 --> 10:00.921
Hey, one minute.
It's a good job. Gives me time to drink.

10:01.600 --> 10:03.284
Think, I said think!

10:03.520 --> 10:06.364
About whatever. I've got my degree,
I can do what I want.

10:06.440 --> 10:08.761
Look, I've gotta go, I'm late.
Yep, I love you too.

10:08.840 --> 10:09.887
5Ye- Bye, bye, bye.

10:10.600 --> 10:11.761
Sorry.

10:13.320 --> 10:14.526
See ya.

10:14.640 --> 10:16.927
Can I help you, sir? Table for one?

10:31.880 --> 10:33.370
Almost there.

10:34.680 --> 10:36.091
How did you do it?

10:36.680 --> 10:38.045
Slipped.

10:38.360 --> 10:40.283
Doing something strenuous?

10:43.680 --> 10:45.125
Your girlfriend will love the scar.

10:47.320 --> 10:48.765
Sexy.

10:49.880 --> 10:51.006
Wife.

10:52.560 --> 10:54.927
Come back in two days,
take the stitches out.

10:55.480 --> 10:57.050
Might still be here.

10:58.240 --> 10:59.765
Back in a minute with some painkillers.

10:59.840 --> 11:01.080
Yeah.

11:05.640 --> 11:06.971
(Reporter on TV) It's been confirmed

11:07.040 --> 11:10.123
that a suicide bombing
occurred earlier today

11:10.200 --> 11:14.330
at 12:30 in the busy
South London restaurant, Driscoll's.

11:14.400 --> 11:17.210
With currently confirmed casualties
of 20

11:17.280 --> 11:19.567
and with more understood
to be injured.

11:19.640 --> 11:22.450
The restaurant was full
of lunchtime customers,

11:22.560 --> 11:24.369
including a large meeting being held

11:24.440 --> 11:26.568
by the 2004 Committee,

11:26.640 --> 11:29.371
an organization which had
Middle East energy interests

11:29.440 --> 11:32.011
and championed the Iraq war.

11:32.080 --> 11:34.970
Three backbench MPs were members.

11:35.080 --> 11:38.129
All are believed
to be amongst the fatalities.

11:38.760 --> 11:41.889
The same Semtex that was
stolen was used in the bombing.

11:44.960 --> 11:48.089
An element in Whitehall feels that
Obama's inclusive doctrine

11:48.160 --> 11:51.881
has spread across the Atlantic
and has made us complacent.

11:52.000 --> 11:54.321
They're pushing for sweeping changes.

11:56.600 --> 12:00.047
If they discover that the Semtex
was being monitored by us

12:00.120 --> 12:01.963
and that we could have stopped it...

12:03.840 --> 12:06.127
I don't need to tell you
the repercussions for this government,

12:06.200 --> 12:08.089
especially with the election looming.

12:08.160 --> 12:10.401
The clock is ticking on all of us.

12:14.920 --> 12:16.888
It's just you and I here, Charlotte.

12:18.920 --> 12:20.843
What can you do for me?

12:33.600 --> 12:37.810
We are here to remember
Corporal Peter Walcott Tiernan,

12:38.600 --> 12:42.525
taken from us in the service of Queen
and country in Afghanistan.

12:44.160 --> 12:49.451
He bravely answered his country's call,
and leaves a loving wife, Louise,

12:49.520 --> 12:52.330
his brothers, Ian and Daniel,
and his mother, Margaret.

12:52.800 --> 12:57.283
It's at times like these that
we must find strength and peace

12:58.080 --> 13:00.367
in the memories
of what he meant to us,

13:00.440 --> 13:02.727
an honorable son and brother.

13:06.320 --> 13:10.882
He was older than his 25 years
and was the one his family relied upon

13:10.960 --> 13:13.281
since losing their father at an early age.

13:13.760 --> 13:16.809
He undertook his responsibilities
with dignity and strength

13:16.880 --> 13:19.451
and maintained a strong family bond.

13:24.440 --> 13:26.886
Remember he said
he had a trial for United?

13:28.520 --> 13:30.568
He said he missed out
cos he was too fast.

13:32.480 --> 13:33.970
You remember, sir?

13:34.120 --> 13:35.645
Yeah, I remember.

13:36.640 --> 13:38.529
Last letter I got from him, he...

13:39.200 --> 13:41.407
He said the regiment
weren't the same since you left.

13:43.680 --> 13:46.650
- How are you, mate?
- How do I look like I am?

13:48.360 --> 13:50.203
Cold makes it hurt like a bastard.

13:50.360 --> 13:52.283
I can't sleep properly.

13:53.120 --> 13:54.724
What happened there?

13:55.600 --> 13:57.523
Ah, some stupid accident.

13:59.760 --> 14:01.444
- Is that your wife?
- Yeah.

14:01.880 --> 14:03.484
Thinks I'm some sort of invalid.

14:03.560 --> 14:04.971
She can't stop fussing.

14:05.520 --> 14:06.851
You should be thankful.

14:07.680 --> 14:09.842
See that bomb they set off in London?

14:10.360 --> 14:14.081
It was on the news.
It never ends. None of it.

14:14.160 --> 14:16.128
What was the point of Pete dying, sir?

14:16.480 --> 14:18.482
Dying in some shithole country
for nothing.

14:18.560 --> 14:21.404
- What was the fucking point?
- What's the matter with you?

14:21.480 --> 14:24.563
Have some respect for him,
for his family.

14:25.080 --> 14:29.449
You got hurt, but you're here.
You're alive.

14:33.840 --> 14:35.569
Listen to me,

14:36.360 --> 14:38.044
we move on.

14:38.560 --> 14:41.689
What's here and now,
that's all that matters, all right?

14:43.320 --> 14:45.129
Go back to your wife.

14:50.200 --> 14:51.850
If you need help,

14:52.320 --> 14:53.765
you can always find me.

14:54.520 --> 14:57.251
We stick together, all of us.

14:57.320 --> 15:00.529
Have you moved on, sir?
From what happened?

15:23.760 --> 15:24.966
Hello?

15:25.040 --> 15:27.281
(Charlotte) A car will be downstairs
in 15 minutes.

15:35.920 --> 15:37.001
I'm Mark.

15:52.560 --> 15:54.050
Baby daughter.

16:25.680 --> 16:29.048
Take the path through the wood.
You'll find her at the other end.

16:31.240 --> 16:32.526
Bit of a walk.

16:34.320 --> 16:37.085
You've seen the news.
20 dead, scores injured.

16:37.960 --> 16:40.691
Semtex was used. You understand?

16:44.640 --> 16:46.483
Perpetrator?

16:46.560 --> 16:48.847
It was strapped to his jacket,
self-detonated.

16:48.920 --> 16:53.721
No details on who he was.
CCTV have no clear images.

16:54.320 --> 16:55.731
There's nothing left of him.

16:55.800 --> 16:57.564
We're bound by procedure.

16:57.880 --> 17:00.360
In this situation,
we cannot afford those constraints.

17:00.440 --> 17:03.683
This is off-reservation.
It's why you're at my home.

17:03.800 --> 17:06.007
I want you to find who's responsible

17:06.079 --> 17:08.890
and stop him
in whatever way you feel fit.

17:08.960 --> 17:10.644
Let it be done quickly.

17:11.920 --> 17:14.605
It'll be you and Mark.
He's young but capable.

17:14.680 --> 17:16.284
Very good with a gun, I hear.

17:16.359 --> 17:19.170
I want it low-tech, old trade craft.

17:20.040 --> 17:22.122
If you get caught,
I don't want evidence.

17:22.319 --> 17:25.130
I'll supply technical backup
and the sweep and clean.

17:25.359 --> 17:29.251
No luck yet with the tracer
you planted in the Semtex

17:29.320 --> 17:32.210
but we did find something curious
of your man Harry.

17:33.160 --> 17:36.130
No bullets in his automatic.
Any thoughts?

17:37.960 --> 17:39.371
Maybe.

17:40.560 --> 17:43.882
You're my hands on this, Ewan,
my conscience.

17:45.640 --> 17:46.721
Wipe it clean.

17:48.280 --> 17:49.725
No loose ends.

18:21.840 --> 18:23.410
Where's Harry?

18:24.000 --> 18:26.207
Fat cheapskate owes me money.

18:28.800 --> 18:30.211
Harry's dead.

18:32.840 --> 18:36.208
I want you to think carefully,
more carefully than you've ever thought.

18:36.280 --> 18:37.645
Was there anything...

18:39.000 --> 18:41.321
Anything unusual happened
in the last few days?

18:41.760 --> 18:45.481
Anything you know
but you're not telling me?

18:45.920 --> 18:47.922
Dead? What are you talking about?

18:55.840 --> 18:56.966
I'm leaving.

18:59.480 --> 19:01.687
You took the bullets from his gun.
Why?

19:01.840 --> 19:03.763
I don't know what you're talking about.

19:09.760 --> 19:12.604
I don't have time to waste.

19:12.680 --> 19:15.251
I know you know something
and I'm not leaving until you talk,

19:15.320 --> 19:18.005
- one way or another.

19:25.600 --> 19:26.726
Talk.

19:26.800 --> 19:29.041
I don't know anything. Please.

19:31.440 --> 19:33.761
By the time I'm through with your face,

19:33.840 --> 19:36.923
nobody's going to wanna look at you,
let alone pay to fuck you.

19:37.880 --> 19:39.769
He said nothing would happen.

19:40.840 --> 19:41.966
What?

19:42.040 --> 19:44.168
- He told me it was just business.
- Who did?

19:44.240 --> 19:47.050
- A client.
- Which client? Tell me about him.

19:47.120 --> 19:49.327
- Young guy, said his name was Paul.
- Paul?

19:49.400 --> 19:52.768
I saw him regular for two months.
He wanted to know stuff about Harry.

19:52.840 --> 19:55.127
- What stuff?
- What he was up to, his routine,

19:55.280 --> 19:56.930
he paid me extra.

19:57.000 --> 20:01.005
I told him useless stuff-
who he met, what time, his routine,

20:01.080 --> 20:03.401
- just useless stuff.
- What about the bullets?

20:03.480 --> 20:05.164
Said it was a joke to take them out.

20:05.240 --> 20:07.527
Said Harry showed up with a gun.
He wanted to teach him a lesson.

20:07.600 --> 20:09.364
Where did you meet him?
What did he look like?

20:09.440 --> 20:11.408
At his house. Expensive place.

20:11.480 --> 20:14.802
Short hair, brown, slim,
could pass for Greek or Italian

20:14.880 --> 20:15.847
but he was an Arab.

20:15.920 --> 20:17.570
- How do you know?
- I have Arab friends.

20:17.640 --> 20:20.564
I know what the language sounds like.
Heard him speaking it on the phone.

20:20.640 --> 20:22.449
You know his address?

20:31.840 --> 20:35.162
When the bomb went off,
there was a flash,

20:35.240 --> 20:37.049
and then there was lots of smoke.

20:37.120 --> 20:40.567
A lot of glass flying. There was
a lot of people on the ground.

20:40.640 --> 20:43.007
Horrendous, huge explosion...

20:43.840 --> 20:46.207
I don't know.
I just felt it more than anything else.

20:52.320 --> 20:53.731
Ash.

20:57.080 --> 20:58.605
Jesus.

20:59.080 --> 21:00.491
How have you been?

21:00.560 --> 21:03.211
Good, yeah. You?

21:03.800 --> 21:05.370
Yeah, I'm good.

21:05.720 --> 21:07.643
Do you, uh, live around here?

21:07.720 --> 21:10.041
No, I'm just... Coffee.

21:11.000 --> 21:12.604
It's good to see you.

21:13.040 --> 21:14.530
Yeah, you too.

21:17.200 --> 21:19.487
I have to go. I'm late for something.

21:19.920 --> 21:22.571
Listen, um... Do you have a number?

21:24.200 --> 21:26.680
If you... If you give me yours, I can...

21:27.560 --> 21:30.006
- If I can get this thing to work.
- It's all right, give me yours.

21:30.080 --> 21:31.366
I'll tap into this.

21:31.440 --> 21:34.364
Um... OK.

21:34.600 --> 21:36.602
07950...

21:38.880 --> 21:40.723
956958.

21:42.440 --> 21:44.408
- Got it.

21:46.640 --> 21:49.325
Look, I have to go.
I'm really late for something, but...

21:50.120 --> 21:51.406
Really nice to see you again.

21:54.240 --> 21:56.846
(Man on TV) Horrific.
What we saw was devastation.

21:56.920 --> 21:59.400
It was just horrific, really.
It was like being in a war zone.

21:59.480 --> 22:01.130
It was crazy and I heard screams.

22:01.200 --> 22:04.124
People like, kind of injured,
and their clothes were all, like...

22:04.200 --> 22:05.531
Everyone was just covered in dust.

22:05.600 --> 22:08.046
(Woman on radio) We have with us
today Crispin Jones,

22:08.120 --> 22:09.610
who is an intelligence expert.

22:09.680 --> 22:12.889
Crispin, what are your thoughts
about the recent spate of bombings?

22:12.960 --> 22:15.964
(Crispin) Well, I think it's too early
for us to speculate

22:16.040 --> 22:17.963
as to who's involved, but, um,

22:18.040 --> 22:19.963
the hallmarks of the bombing
really do point

22:20.040 --> 22:22.202
to home-grown Islamic terrorism.

22:22.320 --> 22:25.085
Cowardly way the bombs were lit
in a public place,

22:25.680 --> 22:28.365
nature of the types of explosives,
and it seems to be...

22:34.680 --> 22:36.170
Off you 9°

23:12.880 --> 23:14.086
Hi.

23:24.080 --> 23:25.889
Can I use your bathroom?

23:27.400 --> 23:28.845
Yeah, you know where it is.

24:34.560 --> 24:36.449
So why are you here?

24:37.480 --> 24:40.689
You always said if I needed any help
I could speak to you.

24:43.400 --> 24:44.970
I need money.

25:01.880 --> 25:03.928
Can I get a drink?

25:06.600 --> 25:08.011
Yeah, sure.

25:41.320 --> 25:42.606
Get your fucking hands up!

25:42.680 --> 25:44.125
- You got me into this!
- Fucking whore!

25:44.200 --> 25:45.611
- Get your hands up!
- Fucking bitch!

25:45.680 --> 25:47.648
- Get away from him!
- You got me into this!

26:04.160 --> 26:05.571
Check outside.

28:10.080 --> 28:12.686
- Hello?
-  Why'd you hang up?

28:13.600 --> 28:15.648
Yeah, I didn't know what to say.

28:15.760 --> 28:18.684
Why didn't you move your lips
and something would have come out.

28:20.960 --> 28:23.167
Listen, are you free to meet?

28:25.320 --> 28:27.561
(Man on radio) It's a bright,
sunny morning in London town,

28:27.640 --> 28:29.369
with highs in the early 20$...

28:31.000 --> 28:34.447
Coming up, lots of new music
and a few other surprises in store!

28:34.520 --> 28:36.727
It's nine minutes past eight...

28:52.480 --> 28:55.484
Time for some music.

28:56.600 --> 28:59.729
It's Blur, from their last album,
Think Tank.

29:05.640 --> 29:07.210
I love this song.

29:07.400 --> 29:10.609
Oh, God, it's gonna stay in my head
for the whole day now.

29:15.520 --> 29:17.204
Shooting star?

29:17.480 --> 29:20.211
It's going out in beautiful flames.

29:31.320 --> 29:34.722
You remember I said
that I was late a couple of weeks ago?

29:36.840 --> 29:37.966
Yeah.

29:38.040 --> 29:40.281
Well, I came on the other day.

29:41.960 --> 29:43.724
Aren't you relieved?

29:46.120 --> 29:47.770
I'm disappointed, actually.

29:52.200 --> 29:56.410
I mean, obviously, that kid would have
my good looks and massive brain.

29:56.480 --> 29:59.245
When do I get to
meet your mum?

29:59.960 --> 30:02.611
Well, you'd have to put
some clothes on first.

30:02.680 --> 30:04.762
You haven't told her
about me, have you?

30:05.520 --> 30:08.444
Is it cos I'm not a nice Muslim girl?

30:09.200 --> 30:10.326
She doesn't know

30:10.400 --> 30:14.246
that you're a bacon-eating,
lager-drinking sex maniac?

30:17.400 --> 30:19.607
John Major signed a peace treaty
with Sinn Féin

30:19.680 --> 30:22.081
because the IRA's violent actions
forced him to.

30:22.400 --> 30:25.802
Gerry Adams changed from a terrorist
to a politician but it was violence

30:25.880 --> 30:29.009
and legal action that forced the change.
Not one lawyer was involved.

30:29.080 --> 30:31.811
Gerry Adams is a murderer.

30:31.880 --> 30:35.043
This is a law class.
It's not a political forum for you to...

30:35.120 --> 30:37.361
Actually, in today's context
he is recognised and accepted.

30:37.440 --> 30:40.410
He's being invited to have tea
with the Prime Minister, for fuck's sake.

30:41.640 --> 30:43.722
Ash, just keep it civilized.

30:44.280 --> 30:45.520
I'm sorry.

30:46.520 --> 30:48.727
Cos he matched them with violence.

30:49.080 --> 30:51.845
I mean, look at Israel,
created through a violent struggle

30:51.920 --> 30:54.571
and now it's an internationally
recognised state.

30:54.640 --> 30:56.642
In America, the American forefathers
fought the British,

30:56.720 --> 30:58.643
beat them hands down,
and now what are they?

30:58.720 --> 31:00.290
They're the biggest
superpower on this planet.

31:00.360 --> 31:02.966
Why? Because violence
is the supreme authority

31:03.040 --> 31:06.010
all authorities derive
their power and legitimacy from.

31:06.600 --> 31:10.446
Law is completely irrelevant
in the face of true force.

